Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated). Pop the @kale{100%g}(chopped) on a large #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{drizzle}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, toss to coat the leaves evenly. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{120%g} and cook, stirring frequently until starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g} and leek to the pan, and cook, stirring frequently until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}, then add the garlic. Stir continuously and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @orzo{180%g} into the pan followed by the @water{450%ml} and the @chicken stock powder{1}.

Bring to a simmer, then reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer until the orzo is cooked and the liquid absorbed, ~{10-12%minutes}. Stir every couple of mins to ensure the orzo is not sticking to the bottom of the pan. If the mixture is looking a bit dry and the orzo is not quite cooked, just add a splash of water and keep cooking.

5 mins before the orzo is ready, pop the kale in the oven to bake until crispy and tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the oven.

Once the orzo is tender, the liquid has been absorbed and the mixture has a lovely creamy texture, remove from the heat and stir in the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated). Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Serve in #bowls{} with the crispy kale on top and enjoy!

> This recipe is a deliciously simple, chef-curated version of Pancetta and Leek Orzotto with a crispy kale topping. Time to bust out the pots and pans!